aps_required:
We can accept official transcripts of 3-year degrees if the degree meets ALL of the following requirements:
- first class
- university / college is NAAC accredited with an "A" grade
- student earned at least 120 total credits or 90 subject credits

As with any degree, we need an official transcript directly from the university. 

If a student's degree does not meet one of these requirements, they are still welcome to submit for a WES evaluation, but it most likely will not come back as equivalent to a U.S. bachelor's degree.
